item.title: ret2win
item.description: $ PYTHONIOENCODING=utf8 ./ret2win.py [!] Pwntools does not support 32-bit Python. Use a 64-bit release. [+] Starting local process './ret2win32': pid 26910 ret2win by ROP Emporium x86 For my first trick, I will attempt to fit 56 bytes of user input into 32 bytes of stack buffer! What could possibly go wrong? You there, may I have your input please? And don't worry about null bytes, we're using read()! > Thank you!
